#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:474
#: c2fe01663ca24af5b0dce6317d3e8708
msgid ""
"The reason the pipeline matters even when you only use "
":class:`~tensormesh.Transformation` is that **each attribute has a fixed "
"cost and a fixed memory footprint**, both controlled by exactly two knobs: "
"the element type (sets :math:`N_b`) and the quadrature order (sets "
":math:`N_q`). When you write a custom assembler and reach for "
"``t.shape_grad``, you now know that what you are holding is a :math:`[N_e, "
"N_q, N_b, D]` tensor built by composing ``get_basis_grad_fns`` (Step 3) with"
" ``get_quadrature`` (Step 4) and the per-element inverse Jacobian (Step 6)."
msgstr ""
"即便你只使用 :class:`~tensormesh.Transformation`\\ ，流程仍然重要，原因在于 "
"**每个属性都有固定的开销和固定的内存占用**\\ ，二者都恰好由两个旋钮控制：单元类型（决定 :math:`N_b`\\ ）和求积阶数（决定 "
":math:`N_q`\\ ）。当你编写自定义装配器并取用 ``t.shape_grad`` 时，你现在就知道，手中拿到的是一个 "
":math:`[N_e, N_q, N_b, D]` 张量，它由 ``get_basis_grad_fns``\\ （步骤 3）、\\ "
"``get_quadrature``\\ （步骤 4）以及逐单元的逆雅可比矩阵（步骤 6）组合而成。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:484
#: 952df635a1b44a7da6e4d318b68c893b
msgid ""
"For shorthand TensorMesh aliases ``phi := shape_val``, ``gradphi := "
"shape_grad``, ``J := jacobian``, ``G := jacobian``, ``GxW := JxW`` — useful "
"when transcribing weak forms directly from the math."
msgstr ""
"为方便起见，TensorMesh 提供了别名 ``phi := shape_val``\\ 、\\ ``gradphi := "
"shape_grad``\\ 、\\ ``J := jacobian``\\ 、\\ ``G := jacobian``\\ 、\\ ``GxW := "
"JxW``——在直接从数学公式誊写弱形式时很有用。"

